title: Cupcake Baker Whips Up A Book
text:
Cupcake Baker Whips Up A Book October 5, 2015, 3:35 PM by Angela Kennecke SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
The woman who opened South Dakota first gourmet cupcake shop has published a book. Melissa Johnson has written, "Fingers in the Frosting," which chronicles her life and her business success. 
Johnson opened up Oh My Cupcakes! in Sioux Falls in 2009 and is currently located at the Bridges at 57th Street. She also has a cupcake kiosk in the Empire Mall. Oh My Cupcakes! has been featured in the "Top 100 Cupcake Shops in America" for the past three years. 
Johnson's book release party is scheduled for Friday, October 9 at her store from 5 to 8 p.m. Copies of her book are available in the shop and "Fingers in the Frosting," will soon be released on Amazon.com. Â© 2015 KELOLAND TV. All Rights Reserved.
